.TH LUMI 1 "2026-04-13" "lumiMUX" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lumi \- terminal multiplexer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lumi
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lumi
is a terminal multiplexer with a git-style sub-command architecture.
Each sub-command can also be invoked directly as
.BI lumi- command
(e.g.\&
.BR lumi-new ).
.PP
If no command is given,
.B lumi
prints usage information and exits.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
The following options are accepted by most sub-commands:
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name.
Defaults to
.B 0
if not specified.
.TP
.BI \-m " mode"
UI mode:
.BR screen " (default),"
.BR turbo ,
.BR minimal .
Accepted by
.B new
and
.BR attach .
.SH COMMANDS
.SS lumi new
Create a new session and attach to it.
.PP
.B lumi new
.RB [ \-A ]
.RB [ \-d ]
.RB [ "\-m mode" ]
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.RI [ shell ]
.TP
.B \-A
If the session already exists, reattach to it instead of failing.
.TP
.B \-d
Detach mode.
Create the session and start the server but do not attach.
.TP
.BI \-m " mode"
UI mode passed to
.BR lumi-attach .
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name (default:
.BR 0 ).
.TP
.I shell
Shell command to run inside the new session.
Uses the user's login shell if omitted.
.SS lumi attach
Attach to an existing session.
.PP
.B lumi attach
.RB [ "\-m mode" ]
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.RI [ name ]
.TP
.BI \-m " mode"
UI mode:
.BR screen " (default),"
.BR turbo ,
.BR minimal .
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name (default:
.BR 0 ).
A positional argument may also be used.
.SS lumi detach
Detach a client from its session.
.PP
.B lumi detach
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name (default:
.BR 0 ).
.SS lumi kill
Terminate a session.
.PP
.B lumi kill
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name (default:
.BR 0 ).
.SS lumi list
List active sessions.
.PP
.B lumi list
.PP
Takes no options.
.SS lumi new\-window
Create a new window in an existing session.
.PP
.B lumi new\-window
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.RI [ shell ]
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name (default:
.BR 0 ).
.TP
.I shell
Shell command to run in the new window.
.SS lumi attr
Get, set, delete, or list per-session attributes.
.PP
.B lumi attr
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.B get
.I key
.br
.B lumi attr
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.B set
.I key value
.br
.B lumi attr
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.B delete
.I key
.br
.B lumi attr
.RB [ "\-s name" ]
.B list
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name.
Defaults to the
.B LUMI_SESSION
environment variable, or
.B 0
if unset.
.SS lumi splash
Display an ANSI art splash screen.
.PP
.B lumi splash
.RI [ scene ]
.RI [ name ]
.TP
.I scene
One of
.BR space ,
.BR mountain ,
or
.BR beach .
Chosen at random if omitted.
.TP
.I name
Text displayed on the splash screen (default:
.BR lumiMUX ).
.SS lumi version
Print version information.
.PP
.B lumi version
.PP
Takes no options.
.SS lumi reload
Reload server configuration.
.PP
.B lumi reload
.PP
Not yet implemented.
.SS lumi send\-keys
Send keystrokes to a session.
.PP
.B lumi send\-keys
.PP
Not yet implemented.
.SS lumi send\-input
Send raw input to a pane.
.PP
.B lumi send\-input
.PP
Not yet implemented.
.SH INTERNAL COMMANDS
.SS lumi\-mserver
Single-PTY micro-server process.
Started automatically by
.BR "lumi new" " and " "lumi new\-window" ;
not intended for direct use.
.PP
.B lumi\-mserver
.B \-s
.I name
.RI [ shell ]
.TP
.BI \-s " name"
Session name (required).
.TP
.I shell
Shell command to run.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B LUMI_SESSION
Set inside an attached session to the current session name.
Prevents recursive attach.
Used by
.B lumi attr
as the default session name when
.B \-s
is not given.
